<p>Hurricane Melissa battered parts of Jamaica and the wider Caribbean, leaving large swaths of the island cut off and aid workers struggling to reach isolated communities four days after the storm made landfall . Officials say at least 50 people have died across the Caribbean, with Jamaica’s confirmed toll at 19 and authorities warning the number may rise as teams reach more places . The storm severely damaged homes, power lines and transport routes and destroyed crop fields and fishing infrastructure, prompting plans to deploy field hospitals and international medical assistance to shore up local health services .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/cTUjZXthArhm8Nrrgk0q8I3jL0Y6P4U76D8P6WgX4ij2D1qpbT1IL_lGwgr1J4mBhGmLzLioXWeaEchkh8kC396Ae4uhOCZI_btQ5HBNxefMWr4zNxVmnz17wK6EuGR5OoAvqD1AeUmT31e6i5AIYIkLwI9IHHl5XlHVq94zaU0NNxdmzd-xQZSLibU-QJ7oQzAa2jsymMHlJt5AiKIVyi3XzFJfY-EI' alt='Blocked traffic and blown off roofs in St. Elizabeth Parish, Jamaica, in the aftermath of Hurricane Melissa.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Access and logistics: Rescuers face blocked roads, snapped power lines and blown-off roofs that are slowing deliveries of food and water to isolated communities .</li><li>Medical response: Jamaican officials plan to deploy multiple field hospitals and have requested international health support, with the World Health Organization and countries such as Spain, Canada and India preparing assistance .</li><li>Agriculture damage: Crop fields were widely destroyed and farming communities report heavy losses, adding pressure to local food supply and livelihoods in rural parishes .</li><li>Haiti toll: Haiti’s civil protection authority reported at least 31 deaths from Melissa, contributing to the regional death toll and complicating relief coordination across affected countries .</li></ul><blockquote>I would imagine it’s more… because there are still places that we have had difficulties reaching. - Christopher Tufton</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Jamaican health ministry (Christopher Tufton): Officials said the confirmed death toll in Jamaica stands at 19 but likely understates fatalities because rescue teams cannot yet reach many communities and they are preparing to deploy field hospitals and specialized equipment to affected areas. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1952728/death-toll-rises-to-50-as-jamaica-haiti-reel-from-hurricane-melissa'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>On-the-ground rescuers and aid workers: Rescuers and aid workers reported struggling to reach cut-off communities as roads, bridges and transmission lines were damaged, complicating food and water distribution four days after the storm struck. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251101-aid-workers-struggle-to-reach-communities-cut-off-by-hurricane-melissa'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Farming and fishing communities: Farmers and fishers described catastrophic damage to crops, boats and infrastructure, warning of immediate losses to incomes and local food supplies. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/hurricane-melissa-deals-heavy-blow-jamaicas-farmers-fishers-127103585'>ABC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251101-aid-workers-struggle-to-reach-communities-cut-off-by-hurricane-melissa'>Aid workers struggle to reach communities cut off by Hurricane Melissa</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/aid-efforts-struggle-to-bring-relief-to-parts-of-hurricane-stricken-jamaica'>Aid efforts struggle to bring relief to parts of hurricane-stricken Jamaica</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/hurricane-melissa-deals-heavy-blow-jamaicas-farmers-fishers-127103585'>Hurricane Melissa deals another heavy blow to Jamaica&#x27;s farmers and fishers</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/02/world/americas/jamaica-hurricane-melissa-death-toll.html'>Death Toll Rises From H